SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 302
By Pody
A RESOLUTION to honor Lynn Daugherty upon her outstanding
career in banking.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should honor those
outstanding citizens who have devoted their careers to serving the financial needs of their fellow
Tennesseans; and
WHEREAS, Lynn Daugherty, a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and
integrity, has taken a much-deserved retirement after forty-three years in banking; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Daugherty was a valuable member of the staff of Wilson Bank & Trust
for twenty-one years before retiring from her post as manager; and
WHEREAS, a graduate of Lebanon High School, she earned her degree in banking from
Cumberland University; and
WHEREAS, her many professional accomplishments aside, Lynn Daugherty is most
grateful for the love and companionship she shares with her husband, David Daugherty, who
serves as pastor of Cornerstone Baptist Church, and their two daughters and five grandchildren;
and
WHEREAS, Lynn Daugherty is wholly committed to the highest ideals of our State and
nation, and she is most worthy of our approbation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor Lynn Daugherty upon her outstanding
career in banking, applaud her ongoing service to the Lebanon community as the first lady of
Cornerstone Baptist Church, and extend to her our best wishes for much continued success and
happiness in the years to come.
